      <meta name="description" content="LXD uses systemd socket activation to start the daemon except at installation time where the daemon is started directly.

Systemd defaults to 0666 for its unix sockets instead of respecting umask, leading to /var/lib/lxd/unix.socket being world writable instead of being restricted to the lxd group as it should be.

The fix is simply to specify a mode of 0660 in the systemd unit.

This affects LXD in wily, xenial and trusty-backports. vivid's version is unaffected as we didn't have socket acti..." />
