    <h3>Bug Description</h3>
  </div>

  <div class="yui3-editable_text-text"><p>LXD uses systemd socket activation to start the daemon except at installation time where the daemon is started directly.</p>
<p>Systemd defaults to 0666 for its unix sockets instead of respecting umask, leading to /var/lib/<wbr />lxd/unix.<wbr />socket being world writable instead of being restricted to the lxd group as it should be.</p>
<p>The fix is simply to specify a mode of 0660 in the systemd unit.</p>
<p>This affects LXD in wily, xenial and trusty-backports. vivid&#x27;s version is unaffected as we didn&#x27;t have socket activation back then.</p></div>
  </div>

  
</div>


